    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix protocol timer initialization in VRTSIM server connection flow\n\n### Summary\nThe VRTSIM implementation had an issue with the protocol timer (timing thread) not being started at the correct point in the server connection procedure. The timing thread was being created after waiting for the client to connect to the shared memory channel, rather than immediately after peer information exchange.\n\nThis caused timing inconsistencies in the simulation environment, particularly when measuring protocol latencies and ensuring proper synchronization between the server and client.\n\n### Changes\n- `radio/vrtsim/vrtsim.c`: Moved timing thread creation to occur immediately after shared memory channel creation but before waiting for client connection. Added proper error handling for pthread_create failure and improved cleanup logic in vrtsim_end function.\n\n"
}